Message.Issue:
'BaseWindow.BaseWindow(double, double, string, Styles, bool, uint)' contains a call chain that results in a call to a virtual method defined by the class. Review the following call stack for unintended consequences:
BaseWindow..ctor(Double, Double, String, Styles, Boolean, UInt32) Window.add_Closed(EventHandler):Void Window.add_Resized(EventHandler<SizeEventArgs>):Void Window.SetVerticalSyncEnabled(Boolean):Void

'BaseWindow.BaseWindow(double, double, string, Styles, bool, uint)' contains a call chain that results in a call to a virtual method defined by the class. Review the following call stack for unintended consequences:
BaseWindow..ctor(Double, Double, String, Styles, Boolean, UInt32) Window.add_Closed(EventHandler):Void Window.add_Resized(EventHandler<SizeEventArgs>):Void Window.SetVerticalSyncEnabled(Boolean):Void RenderWindow.SetView(View):Void Window.SetActive(Boolean):Boolean
Modify 'BaseWindow.~BaseWindow()' so that it calls Dispose(false) and then returns.

Provide an overridable implementation of Dispose(bool) on 'Audio' or mark the type as sealed. A call to Dispose(false) should only clean up native resources. A call to Dispose(true) should clean up both managed and native resources.
Modify 'Audio.Dispose()' so that it calls Dispose(true), then calls GC.SuppressFinalize on the current object instance ('this' or 'Me' in Visual Basic), and then returns.
Modify 'Audio.~Audio()' so that it calls Dispose(false) and then returns.

Rule.Name: Do not call overridable methods in constructors
Rule.Description: Virtual methods defined on the class should not be called from constructors. If a derived class has overridden the method, the derived class version will be called (before the derived class constructor is called).
Rule.Resolution: {0} contains a call chain that results in a call to a virtual method defined by the class. Review the following call stack for unintended consequences: {1}

Rule.Description: Types that declare disposable members should also implement IDisposable. If the type does not own any unmanaged resources, do not implement a finalizer on it.
